“Stop and smell the tulips...a calming,meditive, euphoric high brings pain and stress relief fast...Magical Bliss!”
“I feel like it's the type of weed that is going to make you want to sit around in play video games or sleep really really well”
“Not a fan of this strain regardless of grow quality. Spend your money elsewhere.”
“Great strain. Calm while collected with slight eye lag. Great for small doses. Would not go heavy with this one.”

“A good strain, defiantly a must try. Very sticky as in hard to load due to crystal content. Terpenes are present but not a over whelming mouth watering tasty treat. Got one striped bean, very happy with that going straight to garden.”
“Very nice. I felt happy and really calm. Enjoyed it a lot on a nice hike.”
“Very smooth and comes on slow. Very pungent smell.”
“This tastes good and feels good. It starts slowly at the top of the head and works all the way down. Truly sticky and great to mix with!”

“Dutch Treat is to Amsterdam what Exodus Cheese is to London or at least was when I was there a few years back (both places) so things might have changed but in Amsterdam it was what everyone was smoking and it was every where. It's supposed to be a 80/20 indica/sativa but it seems to lean heavily  on that 20%  it starts you out with an uplifting energetic feeling with a pleasant head high that slowly transitions into...”
“this is my most favorite.”
“I'm in love. This is amazing and now a new favorite!”
“This is mostly a sativa high, very strong. The flower smells amazing, some pine and sweetness. Also is beautiful looking.”
“Dutch Treat is fabulous. I read here that it is the most consumed cannabis at shops in Amsterdam - I don't doubt it. This sativa dominant hybrid is the bees knees for happiness and relaxation.”
“Top 3 on my list. its always a super tasty bud with lots of frost, nice and dense. tastes sweet and smells like a candy store almost. I would recommend this strain for everyone.”

“Solid strain! Bought from the grower Phat Panda, and it doesn't disappoint. It hits on all levels of what you want from a quality strain. Relaxation, pain relief, and all around happiness with the moment you are in. Very smooth smoke and exhale... A little dry but the density of the nugs hold a little moisture  in the center that makes for a nice even burn. Try it you'll like it!”
“2nd favorite strain ever, and a parent for my all time favorite. To smell Dutch Treat is to taste it, regardless of how you ingest it. For my anxiety, this strain is an easy go to.”

“I bought this a few weeks ago in Seattle on a recommendation.  I remember it being really good, but I didn't really have time to relax and enjoy it.  Fast forward to this weekend...my Dutch Treat somehow" made it's way with me to Palm Springs for Memorial Day weekend.   I smoked my first bowl at about 9 am (the closest thing I've had to a wake and bake in 30 years)
column4: and went out to the cabana by the pool.  Th e sati...”"

column3: “idk what to review this as since im smoking DT as i write this. currently feeling a high that is not very intense and it does feel like a creeper as it slow and steady to kick in. it is very smoth, smells good, tastes good, and smoking has been smooth and mellow. i am a jew grower and have read that this is a high yielding strain so i highly concider getting a clone or seeds for this strain. so the high is setting in...”

“I enjoy micro dosing through the day which gives me a steady cerebral euphoria throughout the day. life feels richer, senses are heightened with this strain and the intensity only increases with dosage. at the end of a long day a nice joint completely relaxes my mind while leaving my body energized. great for letting loose or calming social anxiety, dancing, whatever.”
“first time trying it and I love it..”
“Music Sound Way Better than its supposed to be 👌👌”
“Great smell, great taste, great high! For me it leans more towards indica. Great for day usage if you have a high tolerance.”
“tastes good with a great euphoric feeling!”
“Makes me happy, talkative,  & motivated!  Good stuff. Makes sleeping hard.”

“Normally, a hybrid heavy on the indica would give me anxiety but this strain is really great for me.  It had a lot of nice, euphoric sativa tones that made me feel up without feeling overwhelmed in social situations.  Great mind and body high.”
“LOVE it!!!!!!”

“Pleasant mood-lifting effects, I found them to be very subtle though, could be an issue with my tolerance though.  This strain is always sold as top-shelf in the la mmj clubs, I've always found it a solid sativa, but prefer something a tad more racy.”

“Good buds that are super dense, a little goes a long way with this and the head change is strong.  I prefer to have several bowls a day but with Dutch Treat I easily got a headache. Not recommended for rolling, but a good strain.”

“Wow. I packed some Dutch treat into my bong and I took two rips and immediately the high slapped me in the face. About 30 minutes later I found myself sitting in my car thinking to myself, wow, I'm really fucking high... This flower is so fucking bomb. I will definitely pick it up whenever I see it!!”
“Top 3 favorite strains thank you to my Dutch friends for this wonderful treat”

“I'm pleased with Dutch Treat.  Need energy and medication at the start of the day, and this strain (I used wax form) doesn't make me feel edgy" like some of the other sativa or hybrids.  Hope it brings out the creativity but some days simply aren't heading in that direction!”"
“sticky sweets”
“it a great high smoke a blunt in my car by myself and now I cant not stop trying to close my eyes”

“The post about this strain not creating munchies was accurate from my experience. This is one of the few strains that don't result in needing to lock up my refrigerator after a dose. 

The high gives me focus and energy.  This is a good one for a slow day at work writing documentation while listening to music. 

I will keep this one in my go to list.”
“Got it for a party. Guests loved it. Not necessarily my bag" but when I entertain it's great to keep around.”"
“Just recently picked this up and its come in handy for keeping me from hitting emotional rock bottom. It's a decent smoke and keeps your head clear while keeping those pesky emotions in check.”
“Overall Pretty good. Hit pretty fast without smoking a lot. smooth taste. Made me feel very relaxed but not to the point of becoming a couch potato.”

“If hyper focus is your game, then this strain has your name. :)

Decent initial head high followed by pleasant and lingering body high (light perception of warmth and non-distracting tingles). 
I primarily bud because I have a plethora of anxiety problems.  This helped enormously - a decent aid when you need to focus on something and absoposilutely must block everything else out.   
Nice low key euphoria helps take m...”

“oh my! love it! just fired up a joint of dt at the pool. 🎱 late night on a Sunday thinking it would relax me. the opposite. i kept hitting my head on things mistakenly! i was too hyper! maybe because i was excited to blow because its been a week, but i love it. had me feeling creative and a nice head high after a half joint to the face. my girl is at the pool asking a bunch of monkey ass questions, so my high is now...”

“hesitantly ordered this one as recommended by one of the budtenders and my expectations were exceeded. I love sativas but this hybrid made me feel AWESOME. slight stoney super fun body high with a happy mental buzz. love this treat!”
“A super nice smoked, just purchased another half. 🔥👌🏻”
“it keeps me uplifted and at peace”
“I got a 36% thc strain and this is really good stuff. it's the perfect relaxation gaming breed.”

“Dutch Treat was great. I felt relaxed yet uplifted as well along with small yet noticeable bursts of energy. The taste was sweet but not to sweet, buds were kind of sticky and moist not dry like some are.”
“One of my favorite lighthearted heavy-hitting strains, at least for someone like myself. Extremely enjoyable with just the right blend of artistry and engagement.”

“I really like the get up an go sativas, and I didn't find that Dutch Treat fit the bill. I'm a big fan of Super Lemon Haze and a budtender suggested Dutch Treat as a comparable strain. But I found Dutch Treat to be a much heavier high; very grounding and emotionally and physically stabilizing, but not the energetic kick I was looking for. 

On the flip side, this didn't induce any paranoia and left me feeling a littl...”

“Very pleasing, mellow buzz that leaves you fully able to cook, carry on a conversation or take a stroll.  Good choice for us boomers, especially if there is a boring party in your immediate future.  Only negative, the good effects only last about an hour, then you get sleepy.  But still quite enjoyable.”

“This is a very tasty strain, has a very minty after taste that lingers for awhile. Definitely hits me more on the sativa end, I feel a body tingle but my mind stayed sharp. Great for pain in my opinion my back and neck were very relaxed and pain free during the high.”
“Very well balanced hybrid. Perfect for early evening creative activities. Uplifting but not anxious, relaxing but not sedating.”
“Now I understand why this is a staple of Amsterdam coffee shops. It gives you a soothing body high while avoiding the strong sleepy effects of indica. Works great for the afternoon”
“I love this strain because of the taste and the frostiness of it!”
“this strain knocked me, my boyfriend and a giant man out in one bowl”
“Looks great.  Smells & tastes good, too.  I felt a pretty good pick-up for being a Sativa.  Good for projects, but start soon after smoking or you might end up just day dreaming.”

“Fweedom Collective has this one down pat! Accept no imitations! Dank, sticky buds with incredible trichomes. This is the most potent strain I have ever smoked. It's the most-expensive strain at Fweedom Collective, but worth every cent because of the superior way it's been grown and cured! It borders on psychedelic! Wow!”
“favorite strain of all time”

“Fweedom Collective has this one down pat! Accept no imitations! Dank, sticky buds with incredible trichomes. This is the most potent strain I have ever smoked. It's the most-expensive strain at Fweedom Collective, but worth every cent because of the superior way it's been grown and cured! It borders on psychedelic! Wow!”

“One of the nicest strains I've had the pleasure to smoke. Dense nugs , a lighter green with darker hairs. The smell is incredible, especially when breaking it up, and it's sure to be a recognizable one in the future. My guess is that it's an indica dominant, made me real sleepy and just complacent. Excellent weed.”

“A really good head high that hits you quick. It's a nice strain to smoke after a late shift at work. Last time I smoked it I was tense and stressed and it got rid of it almost instantly. Did have a little depression toward the end and I was restless while trying to sleep. I fo have insomnia and most of the strains I've smoked help with that but this one not so much. It wasn't that it kept me up, just simply didn't pu...”
“I Love Dutch Treat My Oh My Smells great taste great smokes grreat. ha ha .GMW Johndeezz the Slap God . look out”
“enticing! this leafy green wondercontinent is a a wetdreTHCm to tokers that are looking for something equal parts ravishing and rebuking. i found if you're searching for something exotic”
“One cookie relaxed me for several ours, Body was calm an relaxed all over. I felt very good the whole time.”
“usually pretty dope. good all round choice”
“Too harsh for me; very strong. Didn't care for the high - anxious & tense.  Intensified pain.”
“Great high. Relaxing body high at first and then the mind starts to wonder into total euphoria. I smoke this stuff at night before bed and I sleep like a log.”

“#mike_the_budtender here with another strain review. Auric AG does it again! This Dutch treat has good sized, tight buds that are just covered in crystals. It's a very potent strain that will give you a great body high and a niice calming effect. Everyone needs to try this stain. Ocean greens has eighths for just $45.”
“Calms me down, but not enough to put me asleep if I don't want to.”
“Satisfactory. Good if nothing more exciting is available.”
“The smell sticks out as a staple of green and this couchlocked me as its done several times on the past. I know what I got myself into”

“For an indica dominant hybrid I must say this is an odd in the list of my personal favorite strains. Sweet buttery bliss is how I feel after hitting this strain with my vape. I love the way it soothes me into a happy haze. Can knock you out at higher doses though so chill out.”
“Terpy on the sweet side”
“Great Day time hybrid. Good smooth flavor and gets your mind right!”
“This bud reminds me of why i started smoking its fun. This bud makes you happy, uplifted, euphoric, relaxed, basically everything you look for in a Hybrid. Perfect Hybrid!!!”
“I think this is my new favorite strain.”

“Finally getting around to this long time staple strain. I prefer an indica-dom hybrid (and indicas in general over sativas) but thought I'd try a sativa-dominant strain like Dutch Treat. It has a very clean inhale / taste. Very nice fruity smell out of the container. At just 15.x% THC I was surprised to experience a very pleasant combination mind/body coolness with only one small pipe bowl. I will definitely add this...”
“good”
“Nice cerebral buzz. Perfect for a Netflix and munchie afternoon.  Had to knock it down a star for the unbelievably dry eyes. Keep visine on hand.”
“my favorite hybrid.doesnt help much with pain and it doesnt make me want to get up and do things. but overall very relaxing amd calming. and it smells wonderful.”
“Has a beautiful sweet candy smell. Really nice cerebral high that makes everything just pleasant.”

“Sweet and Potent
This is a great strain, smoked some in the afternoon and it helped me relax, yet stay focused.”

“Dutch Treat is one of my favorite strains! It's a great, but gentle, high that is especially helpful if you have social anxiety. It doesn't give me overwhelming munchies or make me sleepy, but I still feel relaxed and have an appetite! It doesn't have much of a taste or smell, and is very smooth in a bong!”

“Groovy strain, just enough in just the right groove track to keep clearish and upright. 
LOVING it, wake and baked with my cup o joe... perfect.”
“Uplifting mood enhancement with a clear thinking process intact.”
“good”
“Amazing is the only word for this strain. Every stoner needs to try dutch treat. Delicous smoke chocolate sweet smell and taste. The high is great indica relaxing and euphoric.”

“Dutch Treat is our go to for brainstorming sessions, long walks or coffee with friends. TIP: Clean your piece before you try this one because it is damn tasty. Check out our Girl's Guide to Hybrids - http://wp.me/p7ZvOD-8U”

“Though it's not the strongest strain I've ever smoked, it sure is one of my favorites...the sweet smell is seductive and the the high is even better! Great for an evening chill session after a long day at the office”

“Great clean smoke, and a perfect strain for conversational outings!
The dense, sticky buds have an intense smell of sweet fruity pine trees. 
The cerebral high creeps up leaving the consumer to feel uplifted, creative, talkative, focused, and euphoric while reducing stress, anxiety and relaxing the mind.
Smoke produced is clean & smooth. Nice to the taste.
Even after 2 bowls, a third is not out of the picture entirel...”
“love the high from this flower”
“Very nice urb great for depression and low self esteem type of days. Great I thought for an all day smoke took care of the small aces and pains a great strain also for hiking.”

“Smells and tastes like sweet tasty pines leaving an earthy aftertaste. Dense crystal COVERED nugs with loads of red hairs. Whenever I get done breaking up the bud my fingers are always covered in crystals literally feeling like a treat. At first the high felt uplifting, energetic, happy and leaving me tired an hour later. Definitely one of my favorites strains! Thank you europeans.”
“1st time after 2 lean whiskeys. Very powerful & hits quick. Euphoric, strong head high with tingling in hands and feet.”

“GSC was an extremely dense type of bud. Rock hard and the smell was pine like with hints of mint and menthol. It was extremely harsh as well but the stone was powerful. Got me eating everything in sight, not to mention drinking tons of fluids due to coughing alot. At one point I found myself very happy and content with the buzz as I enjoyed a bike ride on a sunny sunday afternoon. To make sure I wasnt just having a g...”

“This is probably one of my favorite hybrids. The sweet, earthy smell, along with the uplifting and relaxed mood it gives you definitely makes up for the name!!! 
Perfect for those social stoner gatherings, stressed out days, or...fuck it...any day is a great day to smoke this hybrid!!!”
“Dutch treat is good, but not as good as the hype made it seem like, however might be due to inexperienced grower.”

“She's initially crossed with Haze or Northern Lights, making some variations hybrid either Indica or Sativa dominant. 

Taste is one of the biggest clues that she's rare. You can detect the northern immediately; the pine and earth grace the nose as the hints of fruit arrive with a resonance of lemon that subtle finishes.

Best used mid-day for a great pick-up,.”

“First, I'm only giving this 3 stars because it makes me VERY tired which I don't like. Think I read somewhere that this strain is 80/20 indica dominant...so it would make sense that it would make me tired. I seem to be particularly sensitive to indicas in terms of feeling tired. Puts me right to sleep, and I sleep like a f***ing rock. Which I hate.
But other than that, I LOVED the way it smoked and tasted. And the fl...”

“One of my favorite hybrid strains. Green Valley Society's Circa 1997 Dutch Treat is definitely the best I've tried. The smell/taste  is reminiscent of sweet eucalyptus undercut w/ a coffee like nuttiness. A well balanced strain with effects that tend to be a bit Sativa leaning. The perfect mid-day treat.”

“Don't let the lower THC percentage fool you. This strain can pack a punch! Has a lot of room for expansion. Gives you a pretty powerful head high within minutes. The effects and medical benefits are pretty spot on to the profile.”
“the strain that i tried was weak and not grown properly, i must try the real deal....”

“this strain is extremely lightweight. I'm disappointed in my purchase of this particular stain. Usually I like to conserve but this is of such bad quality that at this point I'm just rollin blunts of it to burn through and waste it already. Do not spend your money on this strain if you ARE looking for a good buzz. Dutch Treat will not provide what you're looking for. I would recommend this stain to somebody with a ve...”
“Taste was unimpressive by far, mellow high, i'll avoid this strain in the future unless it's part of a hybrid.”
“This stuff made me feel sad and tired, which is kind of a bummer. It smells incredible though!”
“The perfect thing to erase any kind I'd stress”
“Found at HHC”
“So damn good straight flam”
“Very nice, unique body high that shifts you in your seat like Captain Kirk in his swiggle chair. Not an ounce of tension but every ounce of relaxation.”
“It's a good strain, just wouldn't recommend buying it where I get it.”

“Ahhhh Dutch Treat a strain I can always count on! A staple of the cannabis community and a favorite among Pacific Northwesterners. A classic balanced hybrid that offers a relaxed body high and a creative mental buzz that leaves you laid back while attentive and happy.
    The scent and flavors of Pine and Eucalyptus are predominant and expected in this classic terpy treat.  Whether you are out in the wilderness or en...”
“It made me a bit paranoid and down, but could melted my body for sure. Wouldn't get it again unless I was desperado”

“Lost a star for density (an oz looks like a half) 
Lost a star for potency (looks much more potent)
Taste grate and looks very intriguing also makes a lots of sizzling noises which makes it a real treat”
“Strain was good on relaxation and stress. Also helped with nausea, so I can eat more than one meal a day. It was a good high, but not my best.”
“This strain is good, I like it.”

“Pretty strong.  This strain smells similar to chocolope, and has an uknown llineage.

Smells and tastes like chocolope- pretty tasty.

The high is moderate, and probably not the best for morning use, but better for afternoon-night use.  Just my .02”
“Junk, no high”

“Picked this up from a local connect that works and grows for a dispensary and this is definitely some intense stuff. Started out with a big bong bowl in a dark setting which allowed the feeling of a higher body high and then moved to a pipe bowl which still intensified the already amazing high. 

There is a definite euphoric feeling with this and a sense of Déjà vu. When sitting you will feel tingly and as if some ...”
“This is the worst weed I've ever smoked. I started spewing out tar from smoking it and received medical issues. Will not smoke weed ever again.”
